IT&rsquo;S going to be a cold, wet Easter! The South African Weather Service has warned there will be cold weather and thundershowers in most parts of Mzansi. Forecaster Kgolofelo Mahlangu said: &ldquo;There will be a cold front in the Western Cape on Thursday and the rain will continue hammering most provinces.&rdquo; She said on Friday and Saturday, there will be more rainfall in the eastern parts of the country, with windy conditions. &ldquo;We are expecting light rain on Sunday with the skies clearing. &ldquo;There will be little or no rainfall next week.&rdquo; City of Joburg Emergency Services spokesman Robert Mulaudzi said they would be on high alert. He advised residents of Joburg to listen to the radio, watch television and read newspapers to receive updates.